Best Practices for Angular Security
Keep Dependencies Updated: Regularly update Angular and its dependencies to patch security vulnerabilities and benefit from the latest security enhancements.
Input Validation: Always validate and sanitize user input to prevent injection attacks and ensure data integrity.
Use HTTPS: Secure communication between the client and server using HTTPS to prevent data interception and tampering.
Authentication and Authorization: Implement robust authentication mechanisms such as JWT (JSON Web Tokens) and proper authorization to restrict access to sensitive resources.
Avoid Eval and InnerHTML: Avoid using eval() and innerHTML as they can introduce security vulnerabilities. Instead, utilize Angular's built-in sanitization mechanisms.


